{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Metal Ox|kanji=辛丑|romaji=kanoto ushi|onyomi=shinchū|p=xīnchǒu|w=hsin-ch'ou|mi=ɕin⁵³ ʈʂʰoʊ̯|y=san1 chau2|j=san1 chau2|ci=sɐn tsʰɐu̯|mc=sin tʂʰjuw|oc-bs=sin ʈʂʰuʔ}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yin Metal Ox''' (辛丑) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|Sexagenary cycle}}.

It is the 38th combination in the Sexagenary cycle, preceded by {{ill|Gengzi|ja|庚子|lt=Gengzi}} and followed by {{ill|Renyin|ja|壬寅|lt=Renyin}}. In the {{ill|Yin-Yang Five Elements philosophy|ja|陰陽五行思想}}, the Heavenly Stem {{ill|Xin|ja|辛|1=Kanoto (辛)}} represents yin metal and the Earthly Branch {{ill|Chou|ja|丑|1=Ox (zodiac)|lt=Ox (丑)}} represents yin earth; according to the theory of mutual generation (土生金) in the Five Elements philosophy, earth generates metal.

== 辛丑の年 ==
A year is designated as a Yin Metal Ox year when the Western calendar year divided by 60 leaves a remainder of 41.
