In a Western calendar year whose last digit is either 1 or 6 (corresponding to the Heavenly Stems {{ill|Xin|ja|辛|1=Kanoto (辛)|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Bing|ja|丙|1=Hinoe (丙)|12=draft|12=draft}}), the month of December becomes the Yin Metal Ox month. (Note that here “month” may refer either to the month of the old calendar or to a seasonal month defined from {{ill|Xiaohan|ja|小寒|12=draft|12=draft}} until the day before {{ill|Lichun|ja|立春|12=draft|12=draft}}.)

