{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Metal Ox|kanji=辛丑|romaji=kanoto ushi|onyomi=shinchū|p=xīnchǒu|w=hsin-ch'ou|mi=ɕin⁵³ ʈʂʰoʊ̯|y=san1 chau2|j=san1 chau2|ci=sɐn tsʰɐu̯|mc=sin tʂʰjuw|oc-bs=sin ʈʂʰuʔ|qq=}} {{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|qq=}} '''Yin Metal Ox''' (辛丑) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|Sexagenary cycle|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sexagenary cycle|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
It is the 38th combination in the Sexagenary cycle, preceded by {{ill|Gengzi|ja|1=Yang Metal Rat|2=ja|庚子|1=Yang Metal Rat|lt=Gengzi|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gengzi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} and followed by {{ill|Renyin|ja|1=Yang Water Tiger|2=ja|壬寅|lt=Renyin|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Renyin|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. In the {{ill|Yin-Yang Five Elements philosophy|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang Five Elements philosophy|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=}}, the Heavenly Stem {{ill|Xin|ja|辛|1=Kanoto (辛)|lt=Kanoto (辛)|2=ja|3=辛|4=zh|5=辛|1=Kanoto (辛)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Xin|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoto (辛)|qq=}} represents yin metal and the Earthly Branch {{ill|Chou|ja|丑|1=Ox (Zodiac)|lt=Ox (丑)|2=ja|3=丑|1=Ox (zodiac)|lt=Ox (丑)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chou|13=User:Immanuelle/Ox (zodiac)|qq=}} represents yin earth; according to the theory of mutual generation (土生金) in the Five Elements philosophy, earth generates metal.
==Pronunciation== * English: Yin Metal Ox (辛丑) ** Chinese (Mandarin Pinyin): xīnchǒu ** Cantonese (Jyutping): san1 cau2 ** Japanese: ***Kunyomi 1: Kanoto-ushi ***Kunyomi 2: Shinkin-no-ushi ***Onyomi 1: shinchu ** Korean (Revised Romanization, Hangul): sinchuk (신축) ** Vietnamese (Hán-Việt): Tân Sửu
